This repository's own scripts (make_jdic.py and the *_dic_maker.py family,
nvdajp-*.csv custom entries) are licensed as above.

It also contains, under src/nvdajp-jtalk-dic/naist-jdic-source/:
- naist-jdic.csv and the mecab dictionary definition files (char.def,
  feature.def, left-id.def, matrix.def, pos-id.def, rewrite.def,
  right-id.def, unk.def, dicrc): Copyright (c) 2009, Nara Institute of
  Science and Technology, Japan. See COPYING in that directory
  (modified BSD).

It also contains, under src/mecab-src/ (vendored from the Open JTalk
project's fork of MeCab, used to build the mecab-dict-index tool that
compiles the dictionary above):
- Copyright (c) 2001-2008, Taku Kudo; Copyright (c) 2004-2008, Nippon
  Telegraph and Telephone Corporation (MeCab core; BSD/LGPL/GPL
  tri-license, this repository uses the BSD terms). See src/mecab-src/COPYING.
- Additional Open JTalk-specific modifications: Copyright (c) 2008-2011
  Nagoya Institute of Technology, Department of Computer Science
  (same license terms; see file headers under src/mecab-src/src/).

All of the above are compatible with this repository's BSD 3-Clause
license.
